CIM20AHDY-78             is an intermediate-maturing maize hybrid bred for the tropical lowlands of South Asia. This high-yielding, yellow-kernel maize hybrid performs well under heat-plus-drought conditions, and has tolerance to MSR. It demonstrates consistent yield across environments (7.30 t/ha under stress) with good stability across VPD levels and balanced agronomic traits, and only moderate disease response.             
