CIM20AHDY-68             is an intermediate-maturing maize hybrid bred for the tropical lowlands of South Asia. This high-yielding, yellow-kernel maize hybrid performs well under heat-plus-drought conditions, and has tolerance to MSR. It exhibits superior yield under moderate stress (7.59 t/ha) with good relative yield (0.99) plus stable performance across VPD conditions, and robust plant architecture. It is a reliable choice for diverse conditions.             
